# Networking Basics #

"These are some networking basics I learned during my cybersecurity training."

--> Network Topology

Bus Topology = All devices are connected to a single cable.

Star Topology = All devices are connected to a central switch or hub.

Ring Topology = Devices are connected in a circular path.

Mesh Topology = Every device is connected to every other device.

Tree Topology = Combination of star and bus topology.

Hybrid Topology = Combination of two or more topologies.

--> OSI Model

Physical Layer = Transmits data as bits.

Data Link Layer = Transfers data using MAC addresses.

Network Layer = Transfers data using IP addresses.

Transport Layer = Ensures reliable communication.

Session Layer = Manages communication sessions.

Presentation Layer = Converts and encrypts data.

Application Layer = Provides services to end users.

--> IP Address

Private IP Address = Used inside a local network.

Public IP Address = Used to communicate over the Internet.

IPv4 = 32-bit IP address.

IPv6 = 128-bit IP address.

--> Network Ports

Port = A logical communication endpoint used by applications.

HTTP = Port 80

HTTPS = Port 443

FTP = Port 21

SSH = Port 22

DNS = Port 53

SMTP = Port 25
